(last updated 2012-09-23)

Resource Identifier (RI) Scheme name: steam 
Status: provisional

Scheme syntax:
   steam:<command line arguments> or steam://<action>/<id, addon, IP, hostname, etc.>

Scheme semantics:
   Interact with Steam: install apps, purchase games, run games, etc.

Encoding considerations:
   Unknown, use with care.

Applications/protocols that use this scheme name:
   See official documentation from Valve Developer Community website

Interoperability considerations:
   Unknown, use with care.
   May be unsuitable for open use on the public internet.
Security considerations:
   Unknown, use with care.
Contact:
   Registering party: Dave Thaler <dthaler&microsoft.com>
   Scheme creator: Valve Software
Author/Change controller:
   Either the registering party or someone who is verified to represent
   the scheme creator.  See previous answer.
References:
   http://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Steam_browser_protocol

(file created 2012-09-23)